parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the brakes vibrate
the brakes do not stop effectively
the vehicle takes longer to stop than normal
the vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the brakes fail to properly stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to veer off course without assistance, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Popping sound while turning
vehicle veers in the direction of the turn without assistance
vehicle veers either direction on its own on straightaways
loss of pressure on the steering wheel
oversteering
intermittent steering failure when turning right.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause reduced visibility during inclement weather, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wiper motor quits working
the wipers stop working during use

the wipers stop working in the up position
the wipers can be temporarily restarted by moving the wiper switch or hitting the motor.
